value.0: [The man looks at you and speaks softly.] Nice breeze we're having.
[He looks at you intently.] Very good. Take this tome back to Denam.
[The man waves his hand.] You will speak no more.
[You look back for a moment to see the man has vanished. Your head feels light and you feel confused.]
There are stars among the breeze.
There is no breeze among the stars.
But never forget we must cross those bounds.
We have already crossed those bounds.
I will walk away. [You turn to leave.]
Leap higher than a single bound.
It's a little too rainy here for my tastes.
The weather feels great, doesn't it?
